\"from\": 1169, \"to\": 1188}, {\"ngram\": \"his focus\", \"from\": 1205, \"to\": 1214}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 1218, \"to\": 1227}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, both Benjamin Thomas for France, fourth in Tokyo in 2021, and above all Elia Viviani of Italy, whose poor early start in the 2021 Games meant he had to settle for bronze after netting gold five years earlier, will also be key names to watch.\", \"from\": 1229, \"to\": 1479, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1243, \"end\": 1258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benjamin_Thomas_(cyclist)\", \"score\": 0.7746466892489119, \"rank\": 0.23636363636367883, \"text\": \"Benjamin Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benjamin_Thomas_(cyclist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benjamin_Thomas_(cyclist)\"}, {\"begin\": 1263, \"end\": 1269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9277985549356513, \"rank\": 0.07780264157417638, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1281, \"end\": 1286, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.6219399865901238, \"rank\": 0.6078302103467491, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1310, \"end\": 1322, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elia_Viviani\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elia Viviani\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elia_Viviani\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elia_Viviani\"}, {\"begin\": 1326, \"end\": 1331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9732475493159305, \"rank\": 0.026654367206287114, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 2021 Games\", \"from\": 1359, \"to\": 1373}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 1401, \"to\": 1407}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1422, \"to\": 1426}, {\"ngram\": \"key names\", \"from\": 1460, \"to\": 1469}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Changed from a six-event format to four in 2016 and held over a single day, rather than two, for the first time in 2021, the Omnium now consists of a scratch race, a tempo race, an elimination race and a points race.\", \"from\": 1481, \"to\": 1697, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a six-event format\", \"from\": 1494, \"to\": 1512}, {\"ngram\": \"a single day\", \"from\": 1543, \"to\": 1555}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 1578, \"to\": 1592}, {\"ngram\": \"the Omnium\", \"from\": 1602, \"to\": 1612}, {\"ngram\": \"a scratch race\", \"from\": 1629, \"to\": 1643}, {\"ngram\": \"a tempo race\", \"from\": 1645, \"to\": 1657}, {\"ngram\": \"an elimination race\", \"from\": 1659, \"to\": 1678}, {\"ngram\": \"a points race\", \"from\": 1683, \"to\": 1696}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The scratch race is the most straightforward in format, with the order of finishing after 10 kilometres (40 laps) deciding the number of points awarded to each rider.\", \"from\": 1699, \"to\": 1865, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The scratch race\", \"from\": 1699, \"to\": 1715}, {\"ngram\": \"format\", \"from\": 1747, \"to\": 1753}, {\"ngram\": \"the order\", \"from\": 1760, \"to\": 1769}, {\"ngram\": \"10 kilometres\", \"from\": 1789, \"to\": 1802}, {\"ngram\": \"40 laps\", \"from\": 1804, \"to\": 1811}, {\"ngram\": \"the number\", \"from\": 1822, \"to\": 1832}, {\"ngram\": \"points\", \"from\": 1836, \"to\": 1842}, {\"ngram\": \"each rider\", \"from\": 1854, \"to\": 1864}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The tempo race, on the other hand, allows competitors to gain points both in intermediate sprints and by lapping the field.\", \"from\": 1866, \"to\": 1989, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The tempo race\", \"from\": 1866, \"to\": 1880}, {\"ngram\": \"the other hand\", \"from\": 1885, \"to\": 1899}, {\"ngram\": \"competitors\", \"from\": 1908, \"to\": 1919}, {\"ngram\": \"points\", \"from\": 1928, \"to\": 1934}, {\"ngram\": \"intermediate sprints\", \"from\": 1943, \"to\": 1963}, {\"ngram\": \"the field\", \"from\": 1979, \"to\": 1988}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then the elimination race sees the last rider across the line in a sprint held every two laps removed from the event.\", \"from\": 1990, \"to\": 2107, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the elimination race\", \"from\": 1995, \"to\": 2015}, {\"ngram\": \"the last rider\", \"from\": 2021, \"to\": 2035}, {\"ngram\": \"the line\", \"from\": 2043, \"to\": 2051}, {\"ngram\": \"a sprint\", \"from\": 2055, \"to\": 2063}, {\"ngram\": \"every two laps\", \"from\": 2069, \"to\": 2083}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 2097, \"to\": 2106}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the last of the four Omnium events, the most complicated in terms of strategy and the event where most points are awarded, the points race is almost always the most decisive.\", \"from\": 2109, \"to\": 2286, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the four Omnium events\", \"from\": 2124, \"to\": 2146}, {\"ngram\": \"terms\", \"from\": 2172, \"to\": 2177}, {\"ngram\": \"strategy\", \"from\": 2181, \"to\": 2189}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 2194, \"to\": 2203}, {\"ngram\": \"most points\", \"from\": 2210, \"to\": 2221}, {\"ngram\": \"the points race\", \"from\": 2235, \"to\": 2250}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Riders can capture points in a 100-lap race in sprints held every ten laps, as well as gaining and losing points for lapping the field - or being lapped.\", \"from\": 2287, \"to\": 2440, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Riders\", \"from\": 2287, \"to\": 2293}, {\"ngram\": \"points\", \"from\": 2306, \"to\": 2312}, {\"ngram\": \"a 100-lap race\", \"from\": 2316, \"to\": 2330}, {\"ngram\": \"sprints\", \"from\": 2334, \"to\": 2341}, {\"ngram\": \"every ten laps\", \"from\": 2347, \"to\": 2361}, {\"ngram\": \"points\", \"from\": 2393, \"to\": 2399}, {\"ngram\": \"the field\", \"from\": 2412, \"to\": 2421}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As a result, the outright winner is rarely decided before this final round of racing.\", \"from\": 2441, \"to\": 2526, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a result\", \"from\": 2444, \"to\": 2452}, {\"ngram\": \"the outright winner\", \"from\": 2454, \"to\": 2473}, {\"ngram\": \"this final round\", \"from\": 2499, \"to\": 2515}, {\"ngram\": \"racing\", \"from\": 2519, \"to\": 2525}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's fair to say that the Men's Omnium has no clear favourite.\", \"from\": 2528, \"to\": 2590, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2560, \"end\": 2566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omnium\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.338347143952931e-46, \"text\": \"Omnium\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omnium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omnium\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But of all the multiple contenders, veteran Elia Viviani (Italy), gold in 2016 and bronze in 2021, has the best previous Olympic Omnium form and is the only former medallist in the speciality present in this Games' lineup.\", \"from\": 2591, \"to\": 2813, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2635, \"end\": 2647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elia_Viviani\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elia Viviani\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elia_Viviani\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elia_Viviani\"}, {